<p spacebelow="5" metadata="1:1">  <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:1">1:1</span></font></b> Simeon Peter, a slave and apostle of Jesus Christ, to those who have obtained a faith equal in value to ours by the righteousness of our God and Savior Jesus Christ. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:2">2</span></font></b> May grace and peace be multiplied to you in the knowledge of God and of Jesus our Lord, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:3">3</span></font></b> because his divine power has bestowed on us all <i>[things]</i> <i>[that are]</i> necessary for life and godliness, through the knowledge of the one who called us by his own glory and excellence of character, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:4">4</span></font></b> through which things he has bestowed on us his precious and very great promises, so that through these you may become sharers of the divine nature <i>[after]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[after]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;escaping from&rdquo;) which is understood as temporal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> escaping from the corruption <i>[that is]</i> in the world because of evil desire, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:5">5</span></font></b> and <i>[for]</i> this same <i>[reason]</i>, and <i>[by]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[by]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;applying&rdquo;) which is understood as means."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> applying all diligence, supply with your faith excellence of character, and with excellence of character, knowledge, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:6">6</span></font></b> and with knowledge, self-control, and with self-control, patient endurance, and with patient endurance, godliness, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:7">7</span></font></b> and with godliness, brotherly love, and with brotherly love, love. </p>
<p spacebelow="5" metadata="1:8">  <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:8">8</span></font></b> For <i>[if]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[if]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;are&rdquo;) which is understood as conditional."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> these <i>[things]</i> are yours and are increasing, this does not make <i>[you]</i> useless or unproductive in the knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:9">9</span></font></b> For <i>[the one]</i> for whom these <i>[things]</i> <i>[are]</i> not present is blind, being nearsighted, <u>having forgotten the cleansing</u><font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Literally &ldquo;receiving forgetfulness of the cleansing.&rdquo;"><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> of his former sins. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:10">10</span></font></b> Therefore, brothers, be zealous even more to make your calling and election secure, because <i>[if you]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[if]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;do&rdquo;) which is understood as conditional."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> do these <i>[things]</i>, you will never ever stumble. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:11">11</span></font></b> For in this way entrance into the eternal kingdom of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ will be richly supplied for you. </p>
<p spacebelow="5" metadata="1:12">  <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:12">12</span></font></b> Therefore I intend to remind you continually concerning these <i>[things]</i>, although <i>[you]</i> know <i>[them]</i> and are established in the truth that you have. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:13">13</span></font></b> But I consider <i>[it]</i> right, for as long as I am in this habitation, to stir you up by a reminder, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:14">14</span></font></b> <i>[because I]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[because]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;know&rdquo;) which is understood as causal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> know that the removal of my habitation is imminent, as indeed our Lord Jesus Christ made clear to me. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:15">15</span></font></b> And I will also make every effort <i>[that]</i> you are able at any time, after my departure, <u>to recall these things to mind</u><font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Literally &ldquo;to make recollection of these.&rdquo;">.<font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span>  </p>
<p spacebelow="5" metadata="1:16">  <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:16">16</span></font></b> For we did not make known to you the power and coming of our Lord Jesus Christ <i>[by]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[by]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;following&rdquo;) which is understood as means."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> following ingeniously concocted myths, but <i>[by]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[by]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;being&rdquo;) which is understood as means."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> being eyewitnesses of that one&apos;s majesty. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:17">17</span></font></b> For <i>[he]</i> received honor and glory from God the Father <i>[when]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[when]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the temporal genitive absolute participle (&ldquo;was brought&rdquo;)."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> a voice such as this was brought to him by the Majestic Glory, &ldquo;This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.&rdquo; <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:18">18</span></font></b> And <i>[we]</i> ourselves heard this voice brought from heaven <i>[when we]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[when]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;were&rdquo;) which is understood as temporal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> were with him on the holy mountain, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:19">19</span></font></b> and we possess <i>[as]</i> more reliable the prophetic word, to which you do well <i>[if you]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[if]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;pay attention to&rdquo;) which is understood as conditional."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> pay attention to <i>[it]</i> as to a lamp shining in a dark place, until the day dawns and the morning star rises in your hearts, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:20">20</span></font></b> recognizing this above all, that every prophecy of scripture does not come about from one&apos;s own interpretation, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="1:21">21</span></font></b> for no prophecy was ever produced by the will of man, but men carried along by the Holy Spirit spoke from God. </p>
<p spacebelow="5" metadata="2:1">  <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:1">2:1</span></font></b> But there were also false prophets among the people, as there will be false teachers among you also, who will bring in <u>destructive heresies</u><font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Literally &ldquo;heresies of destruction.&rdquo;">,<font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span>  even denying the Master who bought them, <i>[thus]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[thus]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;bringing on&rdquo;) which is understood as result."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> bringing on themselves swift destruction. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:2">2</span></font></b> And many will follow their licentious ways, because of whom the way of truth will be reviled. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:3">3</span></font></b> And in greediness they will exploit you with false words, whose condemnation <i>[from]</i> long ago is not idle, and their destruction is not asleep. </p>
<p spacebelow="5" metadata="2:4">  <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:4">4</span></font></b> For if God did not spare the angels who sinned, but held <i>[them]</i> captive in Tartarus with chains of darkness <i>[and]</i> handed <i>[them]</i> over to be kept for judgment, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:5">5</span></font></b> and did not spare the ancient world, but preserved Noah, a proclaimer of righteousness, <u>and seven others</u><font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Literally &ldquo;eighth.&rdquo;"><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> <i>[when he]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[when]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;brought&rdquo;) which is understood as temporal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> brought a flood on the world of the ungodly, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:6">6</span></font></b> and condemned the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah to destruction, reducing them to ashes, having appointed <i>[them]</i> <i>[as]</i> an example for those who are going to be ungodly, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:7">7</span></font></b> and rescued righteous Lot, worn down by the way of life of lawless persons in licentiousness <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:8">8</span></font></b> (for that righteous man, <i>[as he]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[as]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;lived&rdquo;) which is understood as temporal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> lived among them day after day, was tormenting <i>[his]</i> righteous soul by the lawless deeds <i>[he was]</i> seeing and hearing), <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:9">9</span></font></b> <i>[then]</i> the Lord knows how to rescue the godly from trials and to reserve the unrighteous to be punished at<font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Or &ldquo;until.&rdquo;"><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> the day of judgment, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:10">10</span></font></b> and especially those who go after the flesh in defiling lust<font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Literally &ldquo;in lust of defilement,&rdquo; translated here as an attributive genitive."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> and who despise authority. Bold <i>[and]</i> arrogant, they do not tremble in awe <i>[as they]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[as]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;blaspheme&rdquo;) which is understood as temporal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> blaspheme majestic beings, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:11">11</span></font></b> whereas angels, who are greater in strength and power, do not bring against them a demeaning judgment.<font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Some manuscripts have &ldquo;a demeaning judgment from the Lord.&rdquo;"><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span>  <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:12">12</span></font></b> But these persons, like irrational animals born <i>[only with]</i> natural <i>[instincts]</i> for capture and killing, blaspheming <u>about things</u><font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Literally &ldquo;with reference to which.&rdquo;"><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> they do not understand, in their destruction will also be destroyed, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:13">13</span></font></b> being harmed <i>[as the]</i> wages of unrighteousness. Considering reveling in the daytime a pleasure, <i>[they are]</i> stains and blemishes, carousing in their deceitful pleasures <i>[when they]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[when]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;feast together&rdquo;) which is understood as temporal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> feast together with you, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:14">14</span></font></b> having eyes full of <i>[desire for]</i> an adulteress and unceasing from sin, enticing unstable persons, <i>[and]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[and]</i>&rdquo; is supplied in keeping with English style."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> having hearts trained for greediness. Accursed children! <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:15">15</span></font></b> <i>[By]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[by]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;leaving&rdquo;) which is understood as means."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> leaving the straight path, they have gone astray, <i>[because they]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[because]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;followed&rdquo;) which is understood as causal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> followed the way of Balaam the <i>[son of]</i> Bosor,<font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Although some English versions use &ldquo;Beor&rdquo; here, this is due to harmonization with the Old Testament; the vast majority of Greek manuscripts read &ldquo;Bosor&rdquo; here."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> who loved the wages of unrighteousness, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:16">16</span></font></b> but received a rebuke for his own lawlessness: a speechless donkey, speaking with a human voice, restrained <u>the prophet&apos;s madness</u><font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Literally &ldquo;the of the prophet madness.&rdquo;">.<font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span>  </p>
<p spacebelow="5" metadata="2:17">  <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:17">17</span></font></b> These <i>[people]</i> are waterless springs and mists driven by a hurricane, for whom the gloom of darkness has been reserved. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:18">18</span></font></b> <u>For by speaking high-sounding but empty words</u><font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Literally &ldquo;for speaking pompous <i>[words]</i> of emptiness.&rdquo;">,<font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span>  they entice with desires of the flesh <i>[and]</i> with licentiousness those who are scarcely escaping from those who live in error, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:19">19</span></font></b> promising them freedom <i>[although they]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[although]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;are&rdquo;) which is understood as concessive."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> themselves are slaves of depravity. For to whatever someone succumbs, by this he is also<font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Some manuscripts omit &ldquo;also.&rdquo;"><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> enslaved. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:20">20</span></font></b> For if, <i>[after they]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[after]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;have escaped from&rdquo;) which is understood as temporal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> have escaped from the defilements of the world through the knowledge of the Lord<font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Some manuscripts have &ldquo;of our Lord.&rdquo;"><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> and Savior Jesus Christ, and they are again entangled in these <i>[things]</i> <i>[and]</i> succumb to <i>[them]</i>, the last <i>[state]</i> has become worse for them than the first. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:21">21</span></font></b> For it would have been better for them not to have known the way of righteousness than having known <i>[it]</i>, to turn back from the holy commandment that had been delivered to them. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="2:22">22</span></font></b> The <i>[statement]</i> of the true proverb has happened to them, &ldquo;A dog returns to its own vomit,&rdquo;<font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="A paraphrased quotation from Prov 26:11."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> and &ldquo;A sow, <i>[after]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[after]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;washing herself&rdquo;) which is understood as temporal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> washing herself, <i>[returns]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="The verb &ldquo;<i>[returns]</i>&rdquo; is not in the Greek text, but is an understood repetition from the previous clause."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> to wallowing in the mud.&rdquo;<font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="The source of this quotation is uncertain."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> </p>
<p spacebelow="5" metadata="3:1">  <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:1">3:1</span></font></b> Dear friends, this <i>[is]</i> already the second letter I am writing to you, in <i>[both of]</i> which I am attempting to stir up your sincere mind by a reminder, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:2">2</span></font></b> to remember the words proclaimed beforehand by the holy prophets and the commandment of the Lord and Savior through your apostles, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:3">3</span></font></b> above all knowing this, that in the last days scoffers will come with scoffing, following according to their own desires <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:4">4</span></font></b> and saying, &ldquo;Where is the promise of his coming? For <u>ever since</u><font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Literally &ldquo;from which <i>[time]</i>.&rdquo;"><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> the fathers fell asleep, all <i>[things]</i> have continued just as they have been from the beginning of creation.&rdquo; <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:5">5</span></font></b> For <i>[when]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[when]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;maintain&rdquo;) which is understood as temporal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> they maintain this, it escapes <i>[their]</i> notice that the heavens existed long ago and the earth held together out of water and through water by the word of God, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:6">6</span></font></b> by means of which things the world that existed at that time was destroyed <i>[by]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[by]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;being inundated&rdquo;) which is understood as means."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> being inundated with water. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:7">7</span></font></b> But by the same word the present heavens and earth are reserved for fire, being kept for the day of judgment and destruction of ungodly people. </p>
<p spacebelow="5" metadata="3:8">  <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:8">8</span></font></b> Now, dear friends, do not let this one thing escape your <i>[notice]</i>, that one day with the Lord <i>[is]</i> like a thousand years, and a thousand years <i>[is]</i> like one day. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:9">9</span></font></b> The Lord is not delaying the promise, as some consider slowness, but is being patient toward you, <i>[because he]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[because]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;want&rdquo;) which is understood as causal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> does not want any to perish, but all to come to repentance. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:10">10</span></font></b> But the day of the Lord will come like a thief, in which the heavens will disappear with a rushing noise, and the celestial bodies will be destroyed <i>[by]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[by]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;being burned up&rdquo;) which is understood as means."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> being burned up, and the earth and the deeds <i>[done]</i> on it will be disclosed. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:11">11</span></font></b> <i>[Because]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[because]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;are being destroyed&rdquo;) which is understood as causal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> all these things are being destroyed in this way, what sort of <i>[people]</i> must you be in holy behavior and godliness, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:12">12</span></font></b> <i>[while]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[while]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;waiting for&rdquo;) which is understood as temporal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> waiting for and hastening the coming of the day of God, because of which the heavens will be destroyed <i>[by]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[by]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;being burned up&rdquo;) which is understood as means."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> being burned up and the celestial bodies will melt <i>[as they]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[as]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;are consumed by heat&rdquo;) which is understood as temporal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> are consumed by heat! <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:13">13</span></font></b> But according to his promise, we are waiting for new heavens and a new earth in which righteousness resides. </p>
<p spacebelow="5" metadata="3:14">  <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:14">14</span></font></b> Therefore, dear friends, <i>[because you]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[because]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;are waiting for&rdquo;) which is understood as causal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> are waiting for these <i>[things]</i>, make every effort to be found at peace, spotless and unblemished in him. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:15">15</span></font></b> And regard the patience of our Lord as salvation, just as also our dear brother Paul wrote to you, according to the wisdom that was given to him, <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:16">16</span></font></b> as <i>[he does]</i> also in all his<font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Literally &ldquo;the&rdquo;; the Greek article is used here as a possessive pronoun."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> <font size=4>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Some manuscripts do not explicitly state &ldquo;his.&rdquo;"><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> letters, speaking in them about these <i>[things]</i>, in which there are some <i>[things]</i> hard to understand, which the ignorant and unstable distort to their own destruction, as <i>[they]</i> also <i>[do]</i> the rest of the scriptures. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:17">17</span></font></b> Therefore, dear friends, <i>[because you]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[because]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;know beforehand&rdquo;) which is understood as causal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> know <i>[this]</i> beforehand, guard yourselves so that you do not lose your own safe position <i>[because you]</i><font size=6>&nbsp;</font><span metadata="Here &ldquo;<i>[because]</i>&rdquo; is supplied as a component of the participle (&ldquo;have been led away&rdquo;) which is understood as causal."><font color="blue"><sup shift="-4">@</sup></font></span> have been led away by the error of lawless persons. <b><font color="#969696"><span metadata="3:18">18</span></font></b> But grow in the grace and knowledge of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ. To him <i>[be]</i> the glory, both now and to the day of eternity. Amen. </p>
